1
00:01:16,960 --> 00:01:19,120
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

2
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:20,040
Jump!

3
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:22,440
Lift right!

4
00:01:22,520 --> 00:01:23,800
Left foot up!

5
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:25,080
Right foot up!

6
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:26,880
Leap left!

7
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:28,160
Don't be sluggish.

8
00:01:28,240 --> 00:01:30,600
Don't slack off. Keep it strong and agile.

9
00:01:30,680 --> 00:01:34,320
You need to show strength in your body.

10
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:35,920
But for the head,

11
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,920
you need to shake it naturally.

12
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:40,320
Jump high, drop low.

13
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:43,680
When you land,
your legs need to be stable and strong.

14
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:45,680
Got it? Let's do it again.

15
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:46,920
Lift right!

16
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,200
Left foot up!

17
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:50,200
Right foot up!

18
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:51,440
Leap left!

19
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:53,280
Leap right!

20
00:01:53,840 --> 00:01:55,280
Left foot forward!

21
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:56,760
Right foot forward!

22
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:57,960
Left foot forward!

23
00:01:58,040 --> 00:01:59,400
Leap right!

24
00:01:59,480 --> 00:02:01,120
Left foot forward!

25
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:04,920
Hey!

26
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,080
Grandpa, I'm sorry.

27
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:08,479
That was close.

28
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:11,920
Hey, what are you doing here?

29
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,920
I want to practice the lion dance too.

30
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:16,640
No, you can't. You're a girl.

31
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:19,080
Girls aren't allowed to do the lion dance.

32
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:21,640
Just go do your homework.

33
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:22,960
It's finished.

34
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:26,000
Then go over it one more time.

35
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:29,320
That way, you'll really learn it
and remember it clearly.

36
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:30,480
Do you understand?

37
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:31,760
Yes, Grandpa.

38
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:36,480
Alright, stand in a relaxed posture.

39
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:38,880
Next is the <i>Ma Bu</i> stance.

40
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:40,400
Bring your legs together.

41
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:41,880
Move like this.

42
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:43,800
Like this. Like this.

43
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:46,320
Do it one more time.

44
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:48,320
Keep your toes straight.

45
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:50,360
Clench your fists. Turn them up.

46
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:54,360
Then sweep your arm back,
turning toward your head.

47
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:56,920
Go, go, clench.

48
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,120
Pull in and punch hard.

49
00:02:58,200 --> 00:02:59,960
Clench. Pull.

50
00:03:00,040 --> 00:03:01,040
Boom!

51
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:05,480
- Joi.
- What was that?

52
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:06,760
Pay attention, will you?

53
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:08,040
Good, Kla. Good.

54
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:09,520
You'll have to squat down,

55
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:12,640
- making sure nothing on you falls.
- Mommy.

56
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:14,760
Jump to the left.

57
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:15,800
- Mommy.
- Come on.

58
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:17,440
- Come on.
- Come on.

59
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:18,600
- Come on.
- Come on.

60
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:20,360
Sweep your left arm.

61
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:21,760
Sweep it.

62
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,880
Ting, wait for me.

63
00:03:23,960 --> 00:03:25,280
Squat down.

64
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:26,360
Turn to the right.

65
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:29,480
Do it.

66
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:34,520
Yeah.

67
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:36,760
Kla, Joi. Let me practice too.

68
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:39,160
You want to practice too?

69
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,480
Alright, let's start.

70
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:44,120
- Pull! Hah!
- Hah!

71
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:45,440
Clench! Pull!

72
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:46,920
- Punch!
- Hah!

73
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,800
- Hah!
- Hah!

74
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:51,280
- Hah!
- Hah!

75
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:52,680
- Hah!
- Hah!

76
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:13,760
Am I good at it, Dad?

77
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:15,400
You're great, my girl.

78
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:20,920
Get up.

79
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:24,960
Now you'll be able to defend yourself.

80
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:27,600
Dad, you're so good,
so I have to be good too.

81
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:30,240
Then people will respect
your legacy as a boxer, Dad.

82
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:34,400
Don's much better than me.
He's a professional boxer.

83
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:36,920
I'm just a temple boxer.

84
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:39,280
- What's that?
- I only fight in temples.

85
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:40,360
Wow!

86
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:43,840
Look. Look at Kla.

87
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:46,480
He's got his dad's blood
running through him.

88
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:48,400
Punch!

89
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:50,720
Kick!

90
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,040
Come on, kick!

91
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:55,320
Alright. Guard.

92
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:56,400
Incoming.

93
00:04:59,040 --> 00:04:59,880
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

94
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:01,240
- I'm here.
- <i>Tom saap.</i>

95
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:04,120
Lotus stem soup too.

96
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:05,800
Wow, <i>kaeng om</i>!

97
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:08,080
You've got great food here.
You'll sell well.

98
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:11,280
- Then hurry so we can sell everything.
- Let's go.

99
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:17,560
They're practicing hard, huh?

100
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:21,360
Remember this, Sweetie.

101
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:24,240
It's truly a blessing for our family

102
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:26,320
that Old Man Liang has been kind to us.

103
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:28,880
For years, our family has stayed united

104
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:30,760
here at the Kimhan Lion Dance Troupe.

105
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:34,200
We have jobs and money
to support one another.

106
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:36,640
We owe him a great deal.

107
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:40,360
It's truly a blessing
for us folks from Isan

108
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:43,680
that Old Man Liang built houses

109
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:46,320
we can rent at affordable prices.

110
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:48,760
So we have a place to sleep.

111
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:52,400
We can go out and work for a living,
then come back and live comfortably.

112
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:54,040
We've reduced our expenses significantly.

113
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:58,440
Grandpa's kindness
is as great as a mountain.

114
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:02,520
I love and respect him
as if he were my own father.

115
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:04,600
You kids should do the same.

116
00:06:04,680 --> 00:06:07,040
If there's anything
you can do to repay him

117
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:10,240
or help him in any way,
don't hesitate to do it.

118
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:11,280
Yes, Dad.

119
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:13,560
I know it by heart now.

120
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:14,720
That's good.

121
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,280
Chalit.

122
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,840
You've been living with me
for a long time.

123
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:25,000
Even though we're not related,
we're like family.

124
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:27,240
We may not share the same blood,
but you're my son.

125
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:30,520
You're the one I trust the most.

126
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:33,760
I have nothing to repay you with

127
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:38,000
except the thing I love most

128
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:40,240
in my life.

129
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:44,760
If I asked you

130
00:06:44,840 --> 00:06:47,600
to take over and look after
the lion dance troupe after I'm gone,

131
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:51,560
can you promise to do that?

132
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:54,560
Sure, I can. Absolutely.

133
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:55,840
Grandpa.

134
00:06:56,640 --> 00:06:58,440
You're still in great shape.

135
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:00,240
Please stay with me
for a long time to come.

136
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:05,520
You silly kid.

137
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:10,080
- Come here.
- Come closer to Grandpa. Come.

138
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,880
Let me tell you something.

139
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:19,160
Even though
I won't be with you for much longer,

140
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:24,600
if you remember everything I taught you,

141
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:27,640
it will be just like

142
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,640
I'm with you all the time.

143
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,760
Confucius once said,

144
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:34,920
among all virtues,

145
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:38,440
gratitude

146
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,560
comes first.

147
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:43,880
Gratitude motivates us

148
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:46,680
to do what is virtuous and right.

149
00:07:46,760 --> 00:07:50,600
Then people will praise us,

150
00:07:51,440 --> 00:07:52,760
saying that we are people

151
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:56,680
who were well brought up by our parents.

152
00:07:58,080 --> 00:07:59,520
Do you understand?

153
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:01,120
I do.

154
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:18,480
Grandpa.

155
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:24,360
- Grandpa.
- Dear.

156
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:26,400
- Grandpa.
- Dear. Oh, no.

157
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:28,360
- Dear.
- Grandpa.

158
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:29,280
Old man.

159
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:30,920
Grandpa.

160
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,200
- Grandpa.
- Dear.

161
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:34,200
Old man.

162
00:09:00,280 --> 00:09:04,080
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

163
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:05,640
<i>Come on, come on.</i>

164
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:08,200
- Come stand here.
- Sai, come on.

165
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:09,120
Go on, get in there.

166
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:10,880
- Come.
- Come stand right here.

167
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:23,960
<i>Thank you, Mom and Dad,</i>

168
00:09:24,040 --> 00:09:25,400
<i>for raising me until I grew up.</i>

169
00:09:26,160 --> 00:09:28,880
<i>I promise I'll find a good job</i>

170
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:30,840
so I can support you both.

171
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:34,400
Sis.

172
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:35,560
- Hm?
- Here.

173
00:09:35,640 --> 00:09:37,800
Beautiful flowers for you.

174
00:09:37,880 --> 00:09:40,320
Wow, where did you get these?

175
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:42,440
I picked them around here.

176
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:43,520
Just kidding.

177
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:48,160
- Here you go.
- Mom, Dad, let's eat together.

178
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:49,920
Be careful. It'll spill.

179
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:52,440
Where's Kla and the rest of the troupe?

180
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:53,680
Why didn't he come to eat?

181
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:55,160
I'm not sure…

182
00:10:28,040 --> 00:10:30,400
Taew, here's my graduation gift for you.

183
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:33,200
Thank you.

184
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:41,160
Hey, idiot. Why are you grabbing my hair?

185
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:45,680
I think I'm going to get
a daughter-in-law.

186
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:47,280
<i>You think?</i>

187
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:49,320
She's actually pretty.

188
00:10:50,280 --> 00:10:52,880
Hey, do you think
we should check for an auspicious date?

189
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:55,160
Once we're officially family,

190
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:58,560
I'll be able to help you run the troupe.

191
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:01,520
Right?

192
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:03,440
That's between them. Let them handle it.

193
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:05,040
- I won't get involved.
- Good idea.

194
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:07,800
- I won't get involved again?
- Just planting seeds here.

195
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:10,280
This is great.

196
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:26,520
Welcome, Mr. Natee.

197
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,560
Is the presentation ready yet, Wat?

198
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:30,640
Yes, it's ready.

199
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:31,720
Good. Let's go.

200
00:11:33,680 --> 00:11:35,000
Has Ms. Ploy arrived yet?

201
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:37,960
She's late as always, Mr. Tee.

202
00:11:38,680 --> 00:11:42,720
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

203
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:49,280
The owner of the land
next to the shrine here,

204
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:51,320
his name is Mr. Chalit.

205
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:53,400
He also owns the Kimhan Lion Dance Troupe.

206
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:56,440
As it turns out, this land right here

207
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:58,560
belonged to Old Man Liang,
the former owner.

208
00:11:58,640 --> 00:11:59,680
He didn't have any kids,

209
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:04,000
so he left the lion dance troupe
and the house to Mr. Chalit.

210
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:05,720
Then he should've agreed
to sell it easily.

211
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:08,280
He got the land for free.

212
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:09,920
Why would he refuse?

213
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:12,360
If he agreed, he'd be rich.

214
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:15,560
I heard Ms. Ploy is pressuring him.

215
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:18,280
And if I owned the land,
I'd be even less willing to sell it.

216
00:12:21,040 --> 00:12:22,480
I'm not pressuring him.

217
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:26,320
He's the one raising the price
and refusing to sell.

218
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,480
I think we can make this work.

219
00:12:32,280 --> 00:12:33,360
Alright.

220
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:36,280
I'll talk with the board
about offering him a higher price.

221
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:39,200
My company will cover
the difference on top

222
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:41,920
of the purchase price we agreed on.

223
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:45,560
Well, actually,
I already made him an offer.

224
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:48,200
But he still won't sell.

225
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:52,200
That's how the poor are. As soon as
they get a little, they want more.

226
00:12:53,120 --> 00:12:54,920
So what do you plan to do next?

227
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,320
I want to get this over with
as soon as possible.

228
00:12:58,600 --> 00:13:01,720
Please trust me.
I've been an agent for a long time.

229
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:04,080
That's all there is to it.
I can handle it.

230
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:47,480
Uncle! Uncle Lit!

231
00:14:47,560 --> 00:14:49,800
- Uncle Lit! Something big just happened!
- What?

232
00:14:50,520 --> 00:14:51,840
The president's men
are blocking our entrance.

233
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:57,840
- I'm taking my girl home! Move!
- What is this?!

234
00:14:57,920 --> 00:15:00,280
I need to get to my daughter!

235
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:03,240
- What is this?
- Little girl, don't cry, okay?

236
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:06,600
- Don't cry.
- Assholes! Why are you blocking her way?

237
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:09,040
No! Let go!

238
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:10,560
My girl!

239
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:15,400
Oh my goodness!

240
00:15:18,440 --> 00:15:19,480
Oh my.

241
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:21,080
Oh my goodness!

242
00:15:21,160 --> 00:15:23,000
Over there! Get them!

243
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:27,240
Why would you do this?

244
00:15:27,320 --> 00:15:30,120
Are you bullying us? Bastards!

245
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:32,080
Yeah, take that!

246
00:15:40,560 --> 00:15:43,800
- Yeah! You evil lowlifes!
- Take this!

247
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:50,360
Is this where the dispute is happening?

248
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:14,240
Mr. Natee.

249
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:21,400
Mr. Tee.

250
00:16:22,880 --> 00:16:24,600
No!

251
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:31,640
That's enough!

252
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:34,600
Hey, I told you to stop!

253
00:16:34,680 --> 00:16:35,880
- Stop!
- Hold on!

254
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:39,320
Ms. Ploy, how could you do this?

255
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:40,800
Why block our way in and out?

256
00:16:40,880 --> 00:16:42,360
Why can't I?

257
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:43,920
This is my land.

258
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:45,640
So that's your reasoning?

259
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:49,080
We use this path day and night,
and you're still blocking it?

260
00:16:49,160 --> 00:16:51,080
Did you see Pum? Look how pitiful she is.

261
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:52,760
You won't listen? You want a kick, huh?

262
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:55,880
Stop! Stop! Stop right now!

263
00:16:56,920 --> 00:16:57,960
About this matter,

264
00:16:58,040 --> 00:17:00,160
violence won't solve anything.

265
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:03,520
So what do you want us to do?

266
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:06,480
How far are tycoons like you
going to push us?

267
00:17:10,319 --> 00:17:11,599
What is going on here?

268
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:15,440
- Mr. Chalit.
- Kamnan.

269
00:17:18,720 --> 00:17:20,000
Let's talk at my house.

270
00:17:22,319 --> 00:17:25,319
This is clearly bullying.

271
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:27,680
We work hard from morning to night.

272
00:17:27,760 --> 00:17:29,160
They should show some empathy.

273
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:32,000
Since they won't sell the land,

274
00:17:32,080 --> 00:17:36,040
I just put up a fence around
the land I bought, to mark the boundary.

275
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:39,840
Actually,

276
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:44,200
it's within her rights to do that.

277
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:48,360
I understand, but at the very least,
she should've informed us first.

278
00:17:48,440 --> 00:17:50,240
That way,
we could've found another entrance.

279
00:17:51,160 --> 00:17:52,800
We've been using that path for a decade.

280
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:54,840
Having your men block it like that,

281
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:56,000
doesn't that seem thuggish?

282
00:17:56,080 --> 00:17:58,040
But I'm the landowner now.

283
00:17:58,680 --> 00:18:02,160
If you're having such a hard time,
why don't you sell the land to me?

284
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:06,120
You've already bought
dozens of rai around here.

285
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:08,600
I only have one rai,
are you still going to pressure me?

286
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:09,720
I'm not pressuring you.

287
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:13,680
But my client wants to build
a shopping mall on that land.

288
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:16,000
Since you won't sell,

289
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:18,400
I'll just put up a fence
around my property.

290
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,880
And what exactly did I do wrong?

291
00:18:22,360 --> 00:18:24,560
Or how much would you sell it for?

292
00:18:24,640 --> 00:18:26,200
Name your price.

293
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:30,560
I won't sell.
No matter how much you offer, I won't.

294
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:34,520
Let's think about it this way.

295
00:18:34,600 --> 00:18:38,680
Say they actually do build the mall,

296
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:40,400
how are you going to get into your house?

297
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:44,160
Because the mall definitely
won't let you walk through easily.

298
00:18:44,240 --> 00:18:45,720
They'll close off the area anyway.

299
00:18:51,360 --> 00:18:53,600
I can figure out my own way.

300
00:18:54,760 --> 00:18:57,840
You heard us clearly, right?
No matter what, we're not selling.

301
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:09,320
Alright.

302
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:12,520
I've arranged for a boat
to pick us up at 6:00 a.m.

303
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:14,360
and again at 8:00 p.m., okay?

304
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:16,360
- Okay.
- It'll be a bit tough on the first day.

305
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,480
Come on.

306
00:19:20,560 --> 00:19:21,480
Watch out for the boat.

307
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:22,680
DELICIOUS CURRY AND RICE

308
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:23,880
Go on, get in.

309
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:25,720
My delivery hours are unpredictable.

310
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,440
If I don't get here in time,
it'll cause trouble for the others.

311
00:19:28,240 --> 00:19:31,440
Hey, Joi. We're people
who work hard all day long.

312
00:19:31,520 --> 00:19:33,040
It's tough, but we have to endure it.

313
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:36,760
If I don't make it in time,
I'll have to sleep in my taxi.

314
00:19:36,840 --> 00:19:38,720
I don't have the money
for another boat ride.

315
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:40,360
Oh, Lit.

316
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:42,160
Can I ask you something?

317
00:19:42,960 --> 00:19:44,880
Are there any other solutions?

318
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:46,920
There are a few options, actually.

319
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:49,160
But we'd have to negotiate

320
00:19:49,240 --> 00:19:50,960
and pay them a passage fee.

321
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:54,480
No way. That's too much.

322
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:58,840
Ugh! When are we getting out of here?
I'm so nauseous I could throw up.

323
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:00,320
Calm down, Sai.

324
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:01,600
Everyone, please stay calm.

325
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:04,080
We have to keep fighting together.

326
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:07,240
Right now,
Dad is looking for the best solution.

327
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:08,400
Alright, let's go.

328
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:09,800
Come on.

329
00:20:17,040 --> 00:20:19,560
Natee, this land behind the shrine

330
00:20:19,640 --> 00:20:22,200
is the one the master said
has very good feng shui.

331
00:20:22,840 --> 00:20:26,160
We're going to acquire the land
on both sides of the shrine.

332
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:29,080
If we also get the one behind it,

333
00:20:29,160 --> 00:20:32,160
the entire plot will connect
to the main road over there.

334
00:20:32,240 --> 00:20:34,320
Think about it.
This side is next to the water,

335
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,600
and that side borders the road.

336
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:40,880
A Singaporean company will also invest
with us in a full-service shopping mall.

337
00:20:41,960 --> 00:20:43,480
But the owner of this plot

338
00:20:43,560 --> 00:20:45,200
still hasn't sold it to us yet, right?

339
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:49,840
Not for long.

340
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:54,480
Hey.

341
00:20:55,160 --> 00:20:56,840
Isn't that Chairman Pinyo and his staff?

342
00:20:59,920 --> 00:21:02,160
Just wait till the day I get rich.

343
00:21:02,240 --> 00:21:05,120
I'll switch to a trike
and show it off right in front of them.

344
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:06,920
Damn it.
How long are you going to keep talking?

345
00:21:07,560 --> 00:21:09,080
Let's head out.

346
00:21:09,680 --> 00:21:12,040
- Alright, let's go.
- Gosh.

347
00:21:12,120 --> 00:21:13,680
I'm dizzy too.

348
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:28,920
Whenever there are concert ticket sales,
it's always crowded.

349
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:31,400
Some people have been waiting here
since last night.

350
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:32,760
Didn't they say tickets are expensive,

351
00:21:33,280 --> 00:21:35,280
too expensive for Thai people?

352
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:38,840
It's a trend. Everyone wants to
take pictures to show off.

353
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:41,600
If it were Lisa,
I'd already be in the front row.

354
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:47,640
Whoa, the line is so long.

355
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:56,480
Isn't that Ms. Taew,
Mr. Chalit's daughter?

356
00:22:00,280 --> 00:22:02,640
So she's a K-Pop fan too, huh?

357
00:22:04,440 --> 00:22:06,120
- Hey.
- Excuse me.

358
00:22:06,720 --> 00:22:07,760
Why did you cut in line?

359
00:22:07,840 --> 00:22:08,720
Bullshit.

360
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:10,920
I was waiting here.
You cut in front of me.

361
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:13,680
What are you talking about?
Everyone saw you cut in front of me.

362
00:22:13,760 --> 00:22:16,600
- Idiot, you're talking nonsense.
- Hey!

363
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:19,480
There you go, another fight.

364
00:22:23,240 --> 00:22:24,360
Hey, stop.

365
00:22:24,440 --> 00:22:25,760
Move!

366
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:29,560
Hey!

367
00:22:50,560 --> 00:22:51,600
Security!

368
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:53,680
Ow!

369
00:23:04,040 --> 00:23:05,280
Are you okay, Mr. Natee?

370
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:07,160
I'm fine.

371
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:09,480
Thank you so much, Mr. Natee.

372
00:23:12,040 --> 00:23:13,800
I should be thanking you too, Ms…

373
00:23:14,640 --> 00:23:16,040
Taew.

374
00:23:16,640 --> 00:23:17,480
Thank you, Ms. Taew.

375
00:23:26,320 --> 00:23:28,800
Yes, Or. Payment received.

376
00:23:28,880 --> 00:23:30,600
If you have more jobs, call me anytime.

377
00:23:30,680 --> 00:23:34,760
Whether it's lining up or buying
concert tickets, I've got it covered.

378
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:36,920
Thank you.

379
00:23:37,520 --> 00:23:38,600
Taew.

380
00:23:38,680 --> 00:23:40,160
Bring me along next time too, okay?

381
00:23:40,240 --> 00:23:43,120
Five hours and you get a thousand baht,
that's better than farming.

382
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:44,920
Yeah, let's go.

383
00:23:52,440 --> 00:23:54,280
Hmm!

384
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:57,680
What's with the grin, Mr. Tee?

385
00:23:57,760 --> 00:24:00,320
You almost fell down the escalator.
How are you still smiling?

386
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:03,440
Well, I didn't fall, so I can smile.

387
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:07,440
Were her hands soft?

388
00:24:11,480 --> 00:24:13,320
Soft? They were totally dry and rough.

389
00:24:13,920 --> 00:24:15,400
I bet she's never used lotion.

390
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:17,400
How could they be soft?

391
00:24:17,480 --> 00:24:19,960
Ms. Taew graduated
with a physical education major.

392
00:24:20,040 --> 00:24:24,040
It's no surprise she's tough.

393
00:24:24,120 --> 00:24:25,520
Also,

394
00:24:25,600 --> 00:24:27,600
she's been working to earn money
since she was a kid.

395
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:30,840
She made garlands,
climbed poles, changed light bulbs,

396
00:24:30,920 --> 00:24:32,000
everything.

397
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:34,520
People around there started calling her

398
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:37,880
"the girl with a hundred jobs."

399
00:24:40,360 --> 00:24:42,480
If she needs that much money,

400
00:24:43,160 --> 00:24:45,320
it shouldn't be hard
to convince her to sell the land.

401
00:24:47,520 --> 00:24:48,640
She's a real piece of work.

402
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:52,400
Aside from Mr. Chalit,

403
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:53,800
she's the one

404
00:24:54,480 --> 00:24:57,440
who's being stubborn and refusing to sell.

405
00:25:03,760 --> 00:25:05,560
Can I handle this, Dad?

406
00:25:06,360 --> 00:25:07,840
But don't let him know I'm your son.

407
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:09,320
Otherwise, they'll shut me out.

408
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:12,520
I want them to agree
to sell the land to us willingly.

409
00:25:13,280 --> 00:25:15,760
You don't even use my last name.

410
00:25:15,840 --> 00:25:17,120
Who would know?

411
00:25:17,200 --> 00:25:19,800
I want to prove to everyone
that I'm capable,

412
00:25:19,880 --> 00:25:21,000
that I can do my job well.

413
00:25:21,080 --> 00:25:23,640
If one day
I take over the business from you,

414
00:25:23,720 --> 00:25:25,840
I'll have to earn everyone's respect,

415
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:28,200
not just rely on your name.

416
00:25:29,320 --> 00:25:31,040
Let's see if you can do what you say.

417
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:41,760
Here, Mom.
This is the payment for queueing.

418
00:25:41,840 --> 00:25:43,680
I'll give it to you, in case you need it.

419
00:25:44,400 --> 00:25:46,720
Taew.

420
00:25:46,800 --> 00:25:48,560
Keep it for yourself, honey.

421
00:25:48,640 --> 00:25:50,520
You worked hard to earn it.

422
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:52,520
Save it for later.

423
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:54,920
Your dad and I
still have the strength to work.

424
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:57,800
It's okay, Mom. I want to give it to you.

425
00:25:57,880 --> 00:25:59,200
Keep it, honey.

426
00:25:59,280 --> 00:26:00,840
You keep it.

427
00:26:00,920 --> 00:26:03,040
Then let me hold onto it.

428
00:26:03,120 --> 00:26:04,400
Consider it a school fund.

429
00:26:06,120 --> 00:26:07,360
Mm.

430
00:26:08,040 --> 00:26:09,600
I love you so much, Taew.

431
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:12,640
If you love me, you have to study hard.

432
00:26:12,720 --> 00:26:14,200
Don't just play video games, okay?

433
00:26:14,280 --> 00:26:15,600
I'm not just playing games.

434
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:18,040
I'm working on
a trending business venture.

435
00:26:18,120 --> 00:26:21,320
Soon, I'll be a famous YouTuber.

436
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:22,760
If I get rich, Mom,

437
00:26:22,840 --> 00:26:24,840
I'll buy a car for each of us.

438
00:26:26,040 --> 00:26:29,240
I'll buy a big house
so we won't have to sleep

439
00:26:29,320 --> 00:26:30,600
under bat droppings like this.

440
00:26:31,760 --> 00:26:34,600
Wake up.
I still have to pay for your internet.

441
00:26:38,360 --> 00:26:40,920
- So annoying.
- Your little brother has his own dreams.

442
00:26:55,320 --> 00:26:56,280
Taew, Let me help.

443
00:26:56,360 --> 00:26:57,360
Give it to me.

444
00:27:12,680 --> 00:27:13,680
Here, Dad.

445
00:27:17,960 --> 00:27:18,800
Back off, Taew.

446
00:27:35,600 --> 00:27:36,440
It's okay.

447
00:27:36,520 --> 00:27:38,520
- Okay, switch.
- Hammer.

448
00:27:38,600 --> 00:27:39,840
- Here, Dad.
- Give me a new one!

449
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:42,640
Careful, Dad.

450
00:27:43,760 --> 00:27:44,960
Yay!

451
00:27:47,520 --> 00:27:49,720
- We've got a new exit now!
- A new exit!

452
00:27:52,080 --> 00:27:53,520
How do you like that?

453
00:27:55,800 --> 00:27:58,280
Hold on, hold on.

454
00:27:59,400 --> 00:28:02,200
You can't just break down
the shrine wall to make an entrance

455
00:28:02,280 --> 00:28:04,160
for your own benefit, Mr. Chalit.

456
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:06,040
THE GUAN YU SHRINE

457
00:28:06,120 --> 00:28:08,560
Well, here's the situation, Kamnan.

458
00:28:08,640 --> 00:28:09,760
All of us

459
00:28:09,840 --> 00:28:12,280
have already requested permission
from the foundation,

460
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:17,200
and we've received written approval.

461
00:28:17,280 --> 00:28:19,280
Hey, please show him the documents.

462
00:28:19,960 --> 00:28:22,000
- Here it is.
- The details are inside.

463
00:28:25,120 --> 00:28:28,000
THE GUAN YU SHRINE FOUNDATION

464
00:28:28,080 --> 00:28:29,760
PERMISSION TO BREAK THROUGH
THE SHRINE WALL FOR

465
00:28:29,840 --> 00:28:31,560
AN ENTRANCE AND EXIT
TO KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

466
00:28:34,280 --> 00:28:35,480
Then that's great.

467
00:28:36,280 --> 00:28:38,200
Your family now has a way in and out

468
00:28:38,280 --> 00:28:40,400
without having to take a boat every day.

469
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:42,600
I'm happy for you.

470
00:28:42,680 --> 00:28:44,400
I completely overlooked that.

471
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:46,600
I should've arranged this for you earlier.

472
00:28:48,240 --> 00:28:50,120
Thank you for your understanding, Kamnan.

473
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:51,280
- Right.
- Come on.

474
00:28:51,360 --> 00:28:53,960
- Come.
- It's much easier this way.

475
00:28:54,040 --> 00:28:56,280
It's better than
having to take that detour.

476
00:28:56,360 --> 00:28:57,920
Yeah, Joi.

477
00:28:59,800 --> 00:29:01,520
No need to sweet-talk the rich anymore.

478
00:29:02,400 --> 00:29:04,240
They're just loaded
and completely selfish.

479
00:29:15,760 --> 00:29:17,640
Holy Lord.

480
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:33,560
If you keep that up,
Chalit will come looking for you.

481
00:29:33,640 --> 00:29:35,200
Then keep it down.

482
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:44,880
Five! Do you see the number five?

483
00:29:44,960 --> 00:29:45,800
Five, right?

484
00:29:46,560 --> 00:29:47,720
Eight!

485
00:29:48,240 --> 00:29:50,120
- Eight. It's eight, it's eight.
- Eight. Five and eight.

486
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:51,840
Very clear.

487
00:29:53,160 --> 00:29:55,160
Nine! Nine!

488
00:29:56,520 --> 00:29:58,560
Eight. Five, eight, nine!

489
00:29:59,400 --> 00:30:00,720
Oh my lord.

490
00:30:01,320 --> 00:30:03,800
This draw, let me hit the…

491
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:04,920
Let me hit you instead!

492
00:30:06,520 --> 00:30:08,520
Oh, oh!

493
00:30:08,600 --> 00:30:09,840
Lit!

494
00:30:11,280 --> 00:30:12,800
See that? My numbers changed now.

495
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:14,440
Srikhram, you…

496
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:17,800
My lion head is over a hundred years old,
and now it's all messed up.

497
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:20,000
Why would you sprinkle powder like that?

498
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:28,880
You're obsessed with the lottery, huh?

499
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:34,760
Lit, you don't get it.
Do you know that the lord

500
00:30:34,840 --> 00:30:37,680
is the only hope for poor folks like me?

501
00:30:38,320 --> 00:30:40,640
Whenever I ask for numbers,
he gives them to me every draw.

502
00:30:40,720 --> 00:30:43,480
The only thing you're definitely getting

503
00:30:43,560 --> 00:30:45,120
is a beating at your own shop.

504
00:30:45,880 --> 00:30:47,760
Hurry up and go.

505
00:30:47,840 --> 00:30:49,880
The troupe is coming in
to pay their respects.

506
00:30:50,800 --> 00:30:51,960
Okay.

507
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:54,160
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

508
00:31:07,920 --> 00:31:10,240
May the lion head of Lord Guan Yu

509
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:13,600
protect all members
of the Kimhan Lion Dance Troupe.

510
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:18,600
May the Lion Dance be performed safely
during this year's Vegetarian Festival.

511
00:31:18,680 --> 00:31:23,200
Kimhan Lion Dance Troupe,
may you be great and glorious!

512
00:31:23,280 --> 00:31:27,560
Kimhan Lion Dance Troupe,
may you be great and glorious!

513
00:31:27,640 --> 00:31:32,000
Kimhan Lion Dance Troupe,
may you be great and glorious!

514
00:31:39,600 --> 00:31:43,440
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

515
00:31:52,760 --> 00:31:55,400
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

516
00:32:14,800 --> 00:32:16,880
Here they are,
the Kimhan Lion Dance Troupe.

517
00:32:17,640 --> 00:32:18,920
They're folks from Isan.

518
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:22,040
They make a living
off Old Man Liang's reputation.

519
00:32:22,840 --> 00:32:25,120
Without his name,

520
00:32:25,200 --> 00:32:26,560
no one would probably hire them.

521
00:32:26,640 --> 00:32:28,480
But without passion,

522
00:32:28,560 --> 00:32:30,600
they wouldn't have lasted this long.

523
00:32:30,680 --> 00:32:34,160
No wonder the owner
handed it over to them.

524
00:32:41,200 --> 00:32:42,280
- Wow!
- Hey!

525
00:32:49,320 --> 00:32:51,360
Great. Really great.

526
00:32:52,320 --> 00:32:53,880
Because if he weren't that skilled,

527
00:32:53,960 --> 00:32:55,560
on a pole this tall,

528
00:32:56,240 --> 00:32:58,000
he could've easily fallen to his death.

529
00:33:13,120 --> 00:33:15,280
KIMHAN LION DANCE TROUPE

530
00:33:16,640 --> 00:33:17,680
Okay.

531
00:33:18,840 --> 00:33:20,720
- Let's set it up. Come on.
- Got it?

532
00:33:21,320 --> 00:33:22,720
- I'll do it.
- Wait.

533
00:33:22,800 --> 00:33:23,960
Here! Here!

534
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:25,040
Yeah!

535
00:33:26,840 --> 00:33:28,400
Hey, Joi.

536
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:30,200
Why aren't you practicing?

537
00:33:30,840 --> 00:33:33,240
Ugh, we're all sore. Give us a break.

538
00:33:33,320 --> 00:33:36,000
We know it by heart now.

539
00:33:36,080 --> 00:33:38,000
- I can do it with my eyes closed.
- "I can do it with my eyes closed."

540
00:33:38,600 --> 00:33:40,320
You can do it with your eyes closed?

541
00:33:43,920 --> 00:33:46,720
Come on, show me. Don't just talk big.

542
00:33:53,520 --> 00:33:54,480
What the hell?

543
00:33:59,720 --> 00:34:00,920
Alright.

544
00:34:02,120 --> 00:34:03,880
Why are the head and tail like that?

545
00:34:03,960 --> 00:34:05,640
They're going in different directions.

546
00:34:05,720 --> 00:34:07,880
Didn't you say you had it down already?

547
00:34:07,960 --> 00:34:09,600
No matter how many times, it's the same.

548
00:34:09,679 --> 00:34:12,320
A woman like you can talk.
If you can do it, come show us.

549
00:34:13,199 --> 00:34:14,880
Fine. I'll show you.

550
00:34:16,679 --> 00:34:18,120
Do it properly, Taew.

551
00:34:18,199 --> 00:34:19,480
Yes.

552
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:34,440
Taew! Taew! Stop!

553
00:34:36,920 --> 00:34:38,960
Who let you perform the lion dance, huh?

554
00:34:41,280 --> 00:34:43,320
How many times have I told you?

555
00:34:43,400 --> 00:34:46,120
You can mess around, ride a motorcycle,

556
00:34:46,199 --> 00:34:48,040
even fight if you want,

557
00:34:48,120 --> 00:34:49,679
but you cannot perform the lion dance.

558
00:34:50,480 --> 00:34:52,920
It's a long-standing tradition,

559
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:56,320
women aren't allowed. It's a man's role.

560
00:35:05,840 --> 00:35:08,120
Kla. Show them.

561
00:35:09,040 --> 00:35:10,040
Yes.

562
00:35:22,520 --> 00:35:24,720
Bring the head down.
Help each other move the equipment.

563
00:35:34,400 --> 00:35:36,480
Lit. Lit.

564
00:35:36,560 --> 00:35:37,800
The event is about to start.

565
00:35:37,880 --> 00:35:40,080
I've already checked this pole,
don't worry.

566
00:35:41,160 --> 00:35:43,760
- Then I'll leave it to you, Don.
- Yes.

567
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:45,960
Guys.

568
00:35:46,040 --> 00:35:46,880
Let's move the pole.

569
00:35:46,960 --> 00:35:48,000
Together.

570
00:35:49,480 --> 00:35:50,840
Come on, careful.

571
00:35:53,520 --> 00:35:54,400
Are you Mr. Chalit?

572
00:35:55,680 --> 00:35:58,000
- Hello.
- Hello.

573
00:35:58,080 --> 00:36:00,520
My name is Natee,
from Siam One Shopping Mall.

574
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:02,880
I went to your house earlier,

575
00:36:02,960 --> 00:36:06,360
but Ms. Nongyao said you'd be here,
so I came.

576
00:36:10,760 --> 00:36:12,560
If you're here about the land,

577
00:36:12,640 --> 00:36:14,800
I already told Ms. Ploy I'm not selling.

578
00:36:16,040 --> 00:36:18,520
Take the drum to the event area.
It's about to start. Go.

579
00:36:18,600 --> 00:36:19,880
Yes, Uncle Lit.

580
00:36:27,440 --> 00:36:29,040
May I ask why?

581
00:36:33,160 --> 00:36:36,080
This house was given to me
by a benefactor.

582
00:36:36,160 --> 00:36:37,600
His dying wish was for me

583
00:36:37,680 --> 00:36:39,640
to take care of the people
who've lived here

584
00:36:39,720 --> 00:36:41,640
and relied on his support.

585
00:36:41,720 --> 00:36:43,320
But if you sell it,

586
00:36:43,400 --> 00:36:44,920
you could buy a bigger place

587
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:46,920
and move everyone there, right?

588
00:36:49,600 --> 00:36:50,600
I can't do that.

589
00:36:51,720 --> 00:36:55,080
The people in the troupe
aren't just my tenants.

590
00:36:55,160 --> 00:36:56,720
There are also those living nearby.

591
00:36:56,800 --> 00:36:59,120
If I move,

592
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:00,760
I'd have to start from scratch.

593
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:04,160
I'd need to find new performers,
which wouldn't be easy,

594
00:37:04,760 --> 00:37:07,520
most already belong to other troupes.

595
00:37:07,600 --> 00:37:09,240
The only thing
businesses like yours care about

596
00:37:09,320 --> 00:37:11,280
is pushing us out to somewhere

597
00:37:11,360 --> 00:37:12,480
far away and cheap.

598
00:37:12,560 --> 00:37:16,280
You think poor people like us don't
deserve to live in the heart of the city.

599
00:37:18,800 --> 00:37:19,840
These people

600
00:37:20,440 --> 00:37:21,680
work hard just to get by.

601
00:37:21,760 --> 00:37:24,200
It's convenient for them
to make a living here.

602
00:37:24,280 --> 00:37:28,920
If you make me move,
how are we supposed to make a living?

603
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:31,000
I hope you understand.

604
00:37:39,480 --> 00:37:40,760
Lift!

605
00:38:24,840 --> 00:38:25,960
Hold it up high.

606
00:39:22,840 --> 00:39:23,920
Oh, damn!

607
00:39:24,640 --> 00:39:26,520
- Lit!
- Uncle Lit!

608
00:39:26,600 --> 00:39:28,520
- Lit!
- Get the truck!

609
00:39:28,600 --> 00:39:29,720
Take him to the hospital!

610
00:39:29,800 --> 00:39:31,760
- Uncle Lit!
- No, don't!

611
00:39:31,840 --> 00:39:34,000
Please don't.
You must not move an injured person.

612
00:39:34,080 --> 00:39:36,400
- Call an ambulance, Wat!
- Yes.

613
00:39:36,480 --> 00:39:38,560
Hey, who the hell are you?
Why are you interfering?

614
00:39:38,640 --> 00:39:40,160
What if something happens to him?

615
00:39:40,240 --> 00:39:42,040
- Uncle Lit!
- You can't!

616
00:39:42,880 --> 00:39:45,440
If we move him improperly,
it could be very dangerous.

617
00:39:45,520 --> 00:39:47,760
We don't know
if Mr. Chalit has any broken bones.

618
00:39:47,840 --> 00:39:50,200
It could damage his nerves,

619
00:39:50,280 --> 00:39:52,000
there's a risk of paralysis.

620
00:39:57,080 --> 00:39:58,800
Mr. Chalit? Mr. Chalit?

621
00:39:59,600 --> 00:40:00,600
Mr. Chalit?

622
00:41:14,720 --> 00:41:16,960
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
